We then used 1,600 CSK triples from Quasimodo [quasimodo], human-rated as very typical (score [1,2[), or typical (score [2,3[), or plausible (score [3,4[) as targets. For each of these triples, we masked the objects, and used the fine-tuned BERT model to predict token likelihoods for the mask.